"title": "5408: messenger",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5408",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An individual whose task is to convey information from one person to another. The word “angel” derives from the Greek word for “messenger”. The word “apostle” comes from the Greek work meaning “sent”.</p>\n<h2>Messengers conveying information from one person to another</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:17\">PRO 13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:13\">PRO 25:13</a></strong> <em>There are many references to messengers in this sense.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:3\">GEN 32:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:14\">NUM 20:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:35\">JDG 6:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam23:27\">1SA 23:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:22\">2SA 11:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:13\">2SA 15:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:2\">1KI 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:13\">1KI 22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:3\">2KI 1:3</a> <em>Elijah intercepts the messengers of Ahaziah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:10\">2KI 5:10</a> <em>Elisha sent a messenger with instructions for Naaman's healing</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:32\">2KI 6:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:14\">JOB 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:9\">ISA 37:9</a> <em>Sennacherib sends messengers to Hezekiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:31\">JER 51:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:4\">DAN 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:25\">PHP 2:25</a></p>\n<h2>Messengers from God to humanity</h2>\n<h3>The OT prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:28\">NUM 16:28</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:8\">ISA 6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:18\">DEU 18:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:8\">JDG 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:25\">2SA 12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:7\">1KI 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:13\">2KI 17:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:6\">ECC 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:27\">ISA 41:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:19\">ISA 42:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:16\">ISA 48:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a> <em>the call of Jeremiah</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:25\">JER 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:4\">JER 25:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:4-Jer26:6\">JER 26:4–26:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:4\">JER 44:4</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:17\">EZK 38:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:2\">HAB 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:13\">HAG 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:9\">ZEC 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:1\">MAL 1:1</a> <em>“Malachi” means “my messenger”.</em></p>\n<h3>The priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:7\">MAL 2:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>John the Baptist</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:10\">MAT 11:10</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:27\">LUK 7:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:2\">MRK 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:6\">JHN 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:1\">MAL 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>Apostles and teachers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:1\">GAL 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:34\">MAT 23:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14\">MRK 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:49\">LUK 11:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:5\">ROM 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:13\">ROM 11:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:1\">1TI 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:7\">1TI 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:11\">2TI 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>Angelic messengers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:13\">DAN 4:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:19\">LUK 1:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:11-Judg6:12\">JDG 6:11–6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:5\">1KI 19:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:14\">ZEC 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:6\">ZEC 3:6</a>MAT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:20\">1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:13\">MAT 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:19\">MAT 2:19</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:11\">LUK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:28\">LUK 1:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:9-Luke2:10\">LUK 2:9–2:10</a> <em>The shepherds at Bethlehem heard God's message through an angel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:26\">ACT 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:3\">ACT 10:3</a> <em>Cornelius receives instructions from an angel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:8\">GAL 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:2-Heb2:3\">HEB 2:2–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:1\">REV 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as God's ultimate messenger</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:28-John7:29\">JHN 7:28–7:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:42\">JHN 8:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4\">JHN 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:36\">JHN 10:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:16\">JHN 13:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:8\">JHN 17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:2\">HEB 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:1\">HEB 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>A messenger of Satan</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:7\">2CO 12:7</a></p>",
